{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"664718ef-3b87-42dc-828b-c2b5eeceaf6e","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Unsupported targets in MSTest v3:**\n| Target | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped — .NET 5 is EOL |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped — .NET Core 3.1 is EOL |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET Framework 4.6.2+** or **.NET 6.0+**.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n1. Replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or later) and drop `netcoreapp3.1`.\n2. Replace the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` / `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages with the unified **`MSTest`** package.\n\nIf you still need to test against those older runtimes, you'll have to stay on MSTest v2.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"025a9806-c198-4045-a591-028433595ff1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me recall what I know:\n\n- MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET 6 (for .NET Core/modern .NET) and .NET Framework 4.6.2 or higher.\n- Actually, let me be more precise. MSTest v3 dropped support for:\n  - .NET 5.0 (which is already end-of-life)\n  - .NET Core 3.1 (also end-of-life)\n  - .NET Framework 4.6.2 might still be supported, but I need to verify.\n\nLooking at the actual MSTest v3 requirements: the package was consolidated into a single `MSTest` package instead of separate components, and it only supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above, plus .NET 6.0 and higher. This means .NET 5.0 and .NET Core 3.1 are completely unsupported, so the user would need to drop those target frameworks to upgrade.","outputTokens":610,"requestId":"A032:1619CB:111C7D8:14036DB:69FEA053"},"id":"7b8283de-5260-4eca-bf5c-c0500aa7db36","timestamp":"2026-05-09T02:47:59.591Z","parentId":"06717b84-f127-4d92-8860-955367ab38e0"}
